                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.123/130</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thurston</persName>, in charge of
                        American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-23T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>577. Have assumed charge and have been received by Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>In absence specific instructions and in view of necessity many communications to
                    Foreign Office, have assumed “in charge of American interests”, subject to
                    Department’s approval or substitution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
